      • parse

        public void parse(String value,
                  boolean clear)
        Parse style settings.
        Parameters:
        value - Style settings to parse. Follows same format as style attribute in HTML: multiple settings are separated by ";" with style name and value separated by ":".
        clear - If true, first remove any existing styles.

      • get

        public Map<String,String> get()
        Returns an immutable map of existing styles.
        Returns:
        Map of existing styles. Never null.

      • get

        public String get(String style)
        Returns the value associated with a style.
        Parameters:
        style - Style whose value is sought.
        Returns:
        The associated value, or null if not found.

      • put

        public String put(String style,
                  String value)
        Adds a style and associated value. If the value is null, any existing style is removed.
        Parameters:
        style - The style name.
        value - The new value.
        Returns:
        The previous value for the style, if any.

      • remove

        public String remove(String style)
        Removes the specified style.
        Parameters:
        style - The style name.
        Returns:
        The value for the removed style, if any.

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if no styles are present.
        Returns:
        True if no styles are present.
